transform() with a Named UDF


Rather than an inline lambda, we can also define a named UDF and pass it to .transform():


def demean(s):
    return s - s.mean()

fortune["Rev_centered"] = (
    fortune
      .groupby("Sector")["Revenues_M"]
      .transform(demean)
)

